# Integration Plan: Engine1 + Engine2 + Shared LLM Service

## Architecture

```
  Flutter App (Mobile)
         │
         ▼
  Nginx :80  (192.168.168.108)
    ├── /engine1/*  →  127.0.0.1:8001  (AI-Engine — FastAPI, document tracking)
    └── /engine2/*  →  127.0.0.1:8002  (Charlie-RAG — Django, LGU services)
                            │
                     Both engines call ↓
                            │
                  LLM-Service :8003  (FastAPI)
                    ├── Ollama :11434  (local, primary)
                    └── Gemini API     (cloud, fallback)
```

---

## Current State Analysis

### Engine 1 — [AI-Engine](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/AI-Engine) (FastAPI) → port 8001
| Aspect | Current |
|--------|---------|
| **Framework** | FastAPI + Uvicorn |
| **LLM** | ❌ None — uses scikit-learn intent classifier + hardcoded template responses |
| **Database** | MySQL via SQLAlchemy |
| **Key endpoints** | `POST /api/chat/`, `POST /api/train`, `POST /api/tts`, `GET /api/health` |
| **How it works** | Classifies intent → extracts PDID → fetches doc from DTS API → returns template response |

### Engine 2 — `Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot` (Django) → port 8002
| Aspect | Current |
|--------|---------|
| **Framework** | Django (async views via ASGI) |
| **LLM** | ✅ Calls Ollama **directly** at `192.168.168.108:11434` via `httpx` |
| **Database** | SQLite (conversations, tracked documents, uploaded docs) |
| **RAG** | ChromaDB + BM25 hybrid search, sentence-transformers embeddings |
| **Key endpoints** | `POST /api/chat/`, `POST /api/chat-stream/`, `POST /api/load-history/`, `POST /api/delete-conversation/` |
| **How it works** | Searches RAG + tracked docs → builds system prompt → calls Ollama `/api/chat` → streams SSE response |

### LLM-Service (already created) → port 8003
| Aspect | Status |
|--------|--------|
| **Endpoint** | `POST /api/generate` (prompt + system_prompt → response) |
| **Providers** | Ollama (primary) → Gemini (fallback) |
| **Health** | `GET /api/providers` |

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Engine 2 → Route Ollama calls through LLM-Service

Engine 2 currently calls Ollama **directly** in two places:
- [call_ollama()](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/charlie/views.py#L368-L387) — non-streaming
- [chat_stream_api()](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/charlie/views.py#L396-L470) — streaming SSE

#### [MODIFY] [views.py](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/charlie/views.py)

**Non-streaming** ([call_ollama](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/charlie/views.py#368-388)):
- Replace direct Ollama HTTP call with call to `http://localhost:8003/api/generate`
- Send [system_prompt](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/charlie/prompts.py#196-276) + [prompt](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/charlie/prompts.py#196-276) (combined from conversation messages)
- Keep fallback: if LLM-Service is down, try Ollama directly

**Streaming** ([chat_stream_api](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/charlie/views.py#396-471)):
- ⚠️ The LLM-Service currently only supports non-streaming. Two options:
  - **Option A**: Add a streaming endpoint to LLM-Service (`/api/generate-stream`)
  - **Option B**: Keep streaming calls going directly to Ollama (simpler, streaming is latency-sensitive)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Recommended: Option B** — Keep the streaming SSE path calling Ollama directly for now. The non-streaming path goes through LLM-Service for the Gemini fallback benefit. We can add LLM-Service streaming later.

#### [MODIFY] [.env](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/Charlie-RAG-based-Chatbot/.env.example)
- Add `LLM_SERVICE_URL=http://localhost:8003`

---

### 2. Engine 1 → Add LLM-powered responses via LLM-Service

Engine 1 currently uses template responses. We'll add an LLM mode that enhances responses.

#### [MODIFY] [config.py](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/AI-Engine/app/config.py)
- Add `LLM_SERVICE_URL: str = "http://localhost:8003"`
- Add `USE_LLM: bool = True` (toggle between template and LLM mode)
- Change default `PORT` to `8001`

#### [NEW] `app/services/llm_client.py`
- New module that calls the LLM-Service `/api/generate` endpoint
- Builds a prompt from: intent + entities + document data + system instructions
- Falls back to template response if LLM-Service is down

#### [MODIFY] [conversation.py](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/AI-Engine/app/services/conversation.py)
- After step 5 (fetch document), if `USE_LLM=True`:
  - Build prompt with document data and intent context
  - Call `llm_client.generate()` → LLM-Service
  - Fall back to [generate_response()](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/AI-Engine/app/services/response_generator.py#43-117) (templates) if LLM fails

---

### 3. LLM-Service → Add streaming endpoint

#### [MODIFY] [router.py](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/LLM-Service/app/router.py)
- Add `POST /api/generate-stream` that forwards Ollama streaming

#### [MODIFY] [ollama.py](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/LLM-Service/app/providers/ollama.py)
- Add `generate_stream()` async generator for SSE token streaming

---

### 4. Nginx Configuration

#### [NEW] `nginx/dts-ai.conf`
```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name 192.168.168.108;

    # Engine 1 — Document Tracking (FastAPI)
    location /engine1/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8001/;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    }

    # Engine 2 — LGU/Charlie RAG (Django)
    location /engine2/ {
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8002/;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        # SSE streaming support
        proxy_buffering off;
        proxy_cache off;
    }
}
```

---

### 5. Flutter App → Point to Nginx

#### [MODIFY] [api_config.dart](file:///Users/imziiy/Desktop/2026/CHATAPP_FLUTTER/lib/core/config/api_config.dart)
```dart
static const String engine1Url = 'http://192.168.168.108/engine1';
static const String engine2Url = 'http://192.168.168.108/engine2';
// No more direct Ollama reference needed
```

